subSubSection.paragraph:
Redescription. Live appearance: adult female elongate oval, more or less convex dorsally. Body yellow to yellowish green with dark brown spots on dorsum (the dark spots occasionally lacking). Without visible wax secretion on dorsum before oviposition (
Tanaka et al. 2006
). Ovisac relatively long, about 2–6 times as long as body; posterior part of body not strongly lifted by ovisac.
